                        <date instant="false">Hand a: First half of the 18th cent. (?) Hand b: 20th century (?) Hand c: First half of the 18th cent. (?)</date>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Texts I-a, II-2, II-3, II-4, II-5, III, IV (fol. 3, quires IV-XXI). The handwriting appears irregular throughout the Ms. and changes from careful and neat with broadly spaced letters (quires IV-XV), occasionally in smaller script (fols. 68r-69v, 74r-75v), to mediocre resulting in an uneven script (due to the irregular ruled lines) with narrowly spaced letters (quires XVII-XXI). The quality of rubricated passages also differs (cp. 28v, 68v); often the space left for the name of Mary was not sufficient (cp. 17r, 42v, 68vc, 74vc).  Probably the texts were written at several (three?) stages.</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic"/>
                     <handNote xml:id="h4" script="Ethiopic"/>
                     <handNote xml:id="h5" script="Ethiopic"/>
                     <handNote xml:id="h6" script="Ethiopic">Text I-b = quire II. </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h7" script="Ethiopic">Text II-1 = quire III. The character ሥ is of particular shape (s. fol. 8rb l. 8, 8va l. 6).</handNote>
