                  <persName corresp="PRS0000" instant="false" full="yes">Rǝtuʿǝ ʾAmlak and sometimes Zä-Krǝstos are mentioned in supplication formulas throughout fols. 12ra-89vc, in hand a. It seems that another name has been erased at the beginning of the main textblock (cp. fols. 16vb, 17ra); the name (or parts) of Rǝtuʿǝ ʾAmlak was sometimes written over erasures (cp. fols. 16ra, 16va, 17va-19ra). The names of Sǝbḥat lä-ʾAb and Wäldä Giyorgis are written in supplication formulas on fols. 82rv, 90vc-108vb.&#xD;
In quires XVI-XX, Sǝbḥat lä-ʾAb and Ker ʾƎgziʾ (e.g., fols. 115rb, 117ra, 120rb, 123vc, 129ra, 141rb) as well as Gädä Krǝstos and Kǝflä Giyorgis (e.g., fols. 115rc, 121vc, 125rb, 132vb, 141rc) are mentioned in the supplication formulas.&#xD;
The name of Maḫdärä Krǝstos is written in the supplication formula on fol. 11ra, in hand c.</persName>
